<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="562" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/183.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Dominican Chargé
                            d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge with
                            thanks the receipt of the Minister’s note of the 22d ultimo, in which he
                            encloses for the information of the Department a record of the minutes
                            [etc.].</p>
                        <p>The Department notes that since July 13 of this year there has been no
                            exchange of views between the Plenipotentiaries other than the exchange
                            shown in the remarks recorded under date of August 8 last, enclosed by
                            Señor Peynado as enclosures two and three in his note.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.],</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>